WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.738 --> 00:00:05.439
Principle Vagina:
Mr. and Mrs. Smith.
[ School bell rings ]

2
00:00:05.472 --> 00:00:07.274
thank you for taking time
off work to come in.

3
00:00:07.307 --> 00:00:09.343
So. what's this about.
Principal vagina?

4
00:00:09.376 --> 00:00:11.011
Yeah. what is <i>this</i> about?

5
00:00:11.044 --> 00:00:12.847
You're not a leaner.
You don't have that in you.

6
00:00:12.881 --> 00:00:15.750
Go sit at your desk like the
outer city principal you are.

7
00:00:15.783 --> 00:00:17.251
Morty! Summer! Stop.

8
00:00:17.284 --> 00:00:19.052
Their latest offense
had students

9
00:00:19.086 --> 00:00:21.021
packing their gums
with this --
[ Case beaming lowly ]

10
00:00:21.054 --> 00:00:23.123
This <i>growth</i> gives users
perfect memories.

11
00:00:23.156 --> 00:00:24.993
And there's no right way
to put this...

12
00:00:25.025 --> 00:00:27.027
...the student body
now do nothing

13
00:00:27.060 --> 00:00:30.297
but relive their
intimate achievements.

14
00:00:30.330 --> 00:00:32.466
Student: Yes. more!
More canola oil!

15
00:00:32.499 --> 00:00:35.235
Add to that Morty replacing
himself with ninja clones.

16
00:00:35.269 --> 00:00:37.705
Summer making toilets
chant your weight when you sit.

17
00:00:37.739 --> 00:00:40.407
and this is their third
sci-fi strike this semester.

18
00:00:40.440 --> 00:00:43.076
Morty and Summer
are officially <i>expelled.</i>

19
00:00:43.110 --> 00:00:45.847
Expelled? Can't you just
suspend them with pay?

20
00:00:45.880 --> 00:00:47.381
What has gotten
into you two?

21
00:00:47.414 --> 00:00:49.551
You're unrecognizable
lately --
[ Phone dings ]

22
00:00:49.584 --> 00:00:51.485
[ No audio ]

23
00:00:53.021 --> 00:00:54.789
[ Phone trilling ]

24
00:00:54.822 --> 00:00:56.758
Mom gets red
when she's angry.

25
00:00:56.791 --> 00:00:58.560
Do we have any canola oil?

26
00:00:58.593 --> 00:01:00.127
[ Portal whirs ]

27
00:01:00.160 --> 00:01:01.194
[ Claps ]
Ugh!

28
00:01:01.228 --> 00:01:02.597
Add muting adults to the list.

29
00:01:02.630 --> 00:01:04.298
So I <i>wasn't</i> having
a mental breakdown.

30
00:01:04.331 --> 00:01:05.934
Phew!
Quit summoning me
like this.

31
00:01:05.967 --> 00:01:07.334
People are gonna think
I'm a genie.

32
00:01:07.367 --> 00:01:09.436
Dad. the kids
just got expelled

33
00:01:09.469 --> 00:01:11.506
for being
high-concept assholes.

34
00:01:11.539 --> 00:01:14.509
[ Screams. groans ]
[ Ricktech hoe beaming ]

35
00:01:15.242 --> 00:01:16.644
Turning people into carrots

36
00:01:16.678 --> 00:01:18.211
won't help you beat
the genie allegations.

37
00:01:18.245 --> 00:01:20.213
I won't dignify that
with a response. Jerry.

38
00:01:20.247 --> 00:01:22.249
but I will make you
a carrot at some point.

39
00:01:22.282 --> 00:01:24.018
[ Ricktech hoe beaming ]

40
00:01:24.052 --> 00:01:25.352
Too much. Too much!

41
00:01:25.385 --> 00:01:26.921
My bones were my skin
and my organs were frozen

42
00:01:26.955 --> 00:01:28.523
in the orange marrow
my blood became.

43
00:01:28.556 --> 00:01:30.592
The kids aren't expelled.
They aren't expelled!
Oh. dear.

44
00:01:30.625 --> 00:01:32.694
A! All A's! Every class!

45
00:01:32.727 --> 00:01:34.629
Dad. this is why
they're so spoiled.
[ Whimpering ]

46
00:01:34.662 --> 00:01:36.998
You bail them out before
they ever learn a lesson.

47
00:01:37.031 --> 00:01:39.099
Yeah. you turned out
<i>so</i> awesome without him.

48
00:01:39.132 --> 00:01:40.868
Don't give Rick
that much credit.

49
00:01:40.902 --> 00:01:42.202
he's not <i>bailing us out.</i>

50
00:01:42.235 --> 00:01:43.838
he's being
a lazy piece of shit.

51
00:01:43.871 --> 00:01:45.138
The fuck you just say?
[ Poof ]

52
00:01:45.172 --> 00:01:46.908
Ugh! Little bitch
Ninja-logged me.

53
00:01:46.941 --> 00:01:48.509
See?
Okay. you win.

54
00:01:48.543 --> 00:01:50.612
I heard about this
sleepaway camp off-world

55
00:01:50.645 --> 00:01:52.814
[ Morty screaming in distance ]
that rich people ship
their spoiled kids to.

56
00:01:52.847 --> 00:01:54.147
You're <i>sending</i> them away?

57
00:01:54.181 --> 00:01:56.116
Shouldn't you be
handling it yourself?

58
00:01:56.149 --> 00:01:57.719
[ Screaming grows louder ]
This <i>is</i> me handling it.

59
00:01:57.752 --> 00:01:59.319
You want me to find a switch?
Bend 'em over?

60
00:01:59.353 --> 00:02:00.487
Give 'em the ol' hot seat?

61
00:02:00.521 --> 00:02:02.155
I know
you're being sarcastic.

62
00:02:02.189 --> 00:02:03.323
but I don't like
the excitement in your voice.

63
00:02:03.357 --> 00:02:04.993
Good.
Oh. whatever.

64
00:02:05.026 --> 00:02:06.426
Keep turning your problems
into carrots.

65
00:02:06.460 --> 00:02:08.663
[ Loud crash. screaming stops ]
Beth!

66
00:02:08.696 --> 00:02:09.964
Pack your shit.

67
00:02:09.998 --> 00:02:16.971
♪

68
00:02:17.005 --> 00:02:23.978
♪

69
00:02:24.012 --> 00:02:30.918
♪

70
00:02:30.952 --> 00:02:37.825
♪

71
00:02:37.859 --> 00:02:39.894
[ Electric buzzing ]

72
00:02:42.229 --> 00:02:44.331
[ Feet thumping ]

73
00:02:44.832 --> 00:02:46.466
This is bullshit.

74
00:02:46.501 --> 00:02:48.268
How else are we
supposed to treat our
normie-ass classmates?

75
00:02:48.301 --> 00:02:50.038
We're literally
in space right now.

76
00:02:50.071 --> 00:02:51.371
Yeah. why do we
get punished

77
00:02:51.405 --> 00:02:52.774
for being better
than everyone?

78
00:02:52.807 --> 00:02:54.609
Because <i>you</i> aren't. I am.

79
00:02:54.642 --> 00:02:56.544
You two are remora --
too fucking spoiled

80
00:02:56.577 --> 00:02:58.112
to know you're mooching
off a shark.

81
00:02:58.146 --> 00:02:59.446
Ugh! Whatever. bro.

82
00:02:59.479 --> 00:03:00.682
Me and Summer
have grown so much

83
00:03:00.715 --> 00:03:01.883
we arced onto same page.

84
00:03:01.916 --> 00:03:03.851
But I guess
we haven't grown

85
00:03:03.885 --> 00:03:06.821
as much as your
fucking bald spot.

86
00:03:06.854 --> 00:03:08.156
Yeah. you dumb bitch!

87
00:03:08.188 --> 00:03:09.691
It's pickleball-sized now.
Oh. wow. Wow!

88
00:03:09.724 --> 00:03:12.694
Look at Beyoncé.
rolling up the partition.

89
00:03:13.895 --> 00:03:15.563
[ Phone ringing ]

90
00:03:16.931 --> 00:03:18.766
Ho ho! Did I make the cover?

91
00:03:18.800 --> 00:03:20.267
<i>[ Laughs ] I can't believe</i>
<i>you wanted to.</i>

92
00:03:20.300 --> 00:03:20.968
<i>you fucking loser.</i>

93
00:03:21.002 --> 00:03:22.103
Goddamn it!

94
00:03:22.136 --> 00:03:24.237
His thirsty ass picked up
on the first ring.

95
00:03:24.271 --> 00:03:26.440
[ Loud whooshing ]
What are you doing?

96
00:03:26.473 --> 00:03:29.077
Reminding you who
the shark is.
[ Skin ripping. screaming ]

97
00:03:29.110 --> 00:03:31.579
[ Electronics clattering ]

98
00:03:31.612 --> 00:03:33.081
[ Smoke fizzes ]

99
00:03:33.114 --> 00:03:34.782
[ Machine powers down ]
Oh! Thank God.

100
00:03:34.816 --> 00:03:36.316
[ Groaning ]
It's...over...

101
00:03:36.349 --> 00:03:38.186
[ Chuckles ] If you thought
that dial was bad.

102
00:03:38.218 --> 00:03:39.319
check out this button.

103
00:03:39.352 --> 00:03:40.922
[ Pod snaps shut. buzzes ]

104
00:03:40.955 --> 00:03:42.957
[ Flames roaring. screaming ]

105
00:03:44.992 --> 00:03:47.394
[ Pod clanking. they groan ]

106
00:03:47.427 --> 00:03:48.629
On your feet. maggots!

107
00:03:48.663 --> 00:03:50.732
Move! Move! Move! Move!
Let's go!

108
00:03:50.765 --> 00:03:52.667
Listen. whatever this is.
I can't dig holes all summer.
[ Screams ]

109
00:03:52.700 --> 00:03:54.202
I have gentle hands.
piano player's hands!

110
00:03:54.234 --> 00:03:55.770
Well.
put those hands to work...

111
00:03:55.803 --> 00:03:58.206
Both: ...Doin' whatever
the fuck you want!

112
00:03:58.238 --> 00:04:00.508
[ Laughs ]
So. just to be clear?

113
00:04:00.541 --> 00:04:02.744
[ Guitar playing ]
The kids took
over the camp.

114
00:04:02.777 --> 00:04:05.980
[ Firework squeals ]
Oh! Uh...g- good?

115
00:04:07.081 --> 00:04:09.282
You feel that?
The AC?

116
00:04:09.316 --> 00:04:12.452
Beth. you know. if it's over
65 degrees. I get hives.

117
00:04:12.486 --> 00:04:14.889
No. This is the first time
we've had the house

118
00:04:14.922 --> 00:04:17.225
to ourselves since...

119
00:04:17.257 --> 00:04:19.127
I <i>know</i> she keeps
drugs in here.

120
00:04:19.160 --> 00:04:20.828
She's 17 and hangs out
with my dad.

121
00:04:20.862 --> 00:04:23.131
[ Shelf beeps ]
Ooh. I think
I found some.

122
00:04:23.164 --> 00:04:26.100
Oh. thank God.
I mean -- oh. no.

123
00:04:26.134 --> 00:04:28.268
Not sure what goes
in what orifice.
Ooh.

124
00:04:28.301 --> 00:04:30.470
This looks familiar enough.
[ Cap pops ]

125
00:04:31.939 --> 00:04:33.207
[ Magical twinkling ]

126
00:04:33.241 --> 00:04:35.375
[ Coughing violently ]

127
00:04:35.408 --> 00:04:37.277
[ Joint crackles ]

128
00:04:37.310 --> 00:04:38.880
[ Exhales ]

129
00:04:39.346 --> 00:04:40.948
Still got it.

130
00:04:40.982 --> 00:04:43.584
Huh. Do you feel anything?

131
00:04:43.618 --> 00:04:45.219
I mean...

132
00:04:45.253 --> 00:04:46.921
...I'm feeling...

133
00:04:46.954 --> 00:04:49.624
[ Mystical whooshing ]

134
00:04:49.657 --> 00:04:51.793
[ Giggling ]

135
00:04:51.826 --> 00:04:53.961
...G- great. [ Gasps ]

136
00:04:53.995 --> 00:04:55.730
[ Laughs ]
We should steal a car!

137
00:04:55.763 --> 00:04:57.497
Rick: Beth? Future carrot?
[ Joint sizzles ]

138
00:04:57.532 --> 00:04:59.167
I dropped off
the little freaks.

139
00:04:59.200 --> 00:05:00.935
You two wanna grab a drink?
Shh. [ Giggles ]

140
00:05:00.968 --> 00:05:02.770
[ Laughs ]
We...we aren--

141
00:05:02.804 --> 00:05:04.205
We aren't home.

142
00:05:04.238 --> 00:05:06.007
What? U-oh. Beth. gross.

143
00:05:06.040 --> 00:05:07.542
Just don't reply next time.

144
00:05:07.575 --> 00:05:09.143
[ Door shuts. they giggle ]

145
00:05:09.177 --> 00:05:10.278
Ahh.

146
00:05:10.310 --> 00:05:12.479
How'd Summer
get drugs from Japan?

147
00:05:12.513 --> 00:05:14.849
What even is this stuff?

148
00:05:14.882 --> 00:05:16.449
[ Phone beeping ]

149
00:05:16.483 --> 00:05:18.786
[ Woman vocalizing ]

150
00:05:19.854 --> 00:05:21.222
[ Both chuckling ]

151
00:05:21.255 --> 00:05:23.558
Oh. man. we totally
had you guys.

152
00:05:23.591 --> 00:05:25.026
It's not a real
camp anymore.

153
00:05:25.059 --> 00:05:27.995
We campers overthrew
the counselors years ago.

154
00:05:28.029 --> 00:05:30.097
Years ago.
Yeah. ya goofy hoes!

155
00:05:30.131 --> 00:05:31.532
We run this shit now.

156
00:05:31.566 --> 00:05:33.267
Anything you want? We got.

157
00:05:33.301 --> 00:05:35.236
Anything you wanna do?
You do.

158
00:05:35.269 --> 00:05:37.171
Can I fire a bazooka
on a skateboard?

159
00:05:37.205 --> 00:05:38.539
C'mon.
you know the answer.

160
00:05:38.573 --> 00:05:40.041
Oh. my God.
I'm gonna do it.

161
00:05:40.074 --> 00:05:42.210
So what happened
to the counselors?

162
00:05:42.243 --> 00:05:43.443
Murdered 'em.

163
00:05:43.476 --> 00:05:45.713
[ Bird squawks. skull clatters ]

164
00:05:45.746 --> 00:05:46.714
Fuck.
Oh. God.

165
00:05:46.747 --> 00:05:48.282
That's where we dump our lame.

166
00:05:48.316 --> 00:05:49.784
Pretty sick. right?

167
00:05:49.817 --> 00:05:53.187
Sickly...awesome.

168
00:05:53.221 --> 00:05:55.323
Let's give 'em a tour.
[ Skateboard clinks ]

169
00:05:55.355 --> 00:05:57.225
[ Thuds. grunts ]
Oh. Ow. ow. ow. ow.

170
00:05:57.258 --> 00:05:59.694
Is he okay?
Oh. God. Who gives a shit?

171
00:05:59.727 --> 00:06:00.595
[ Slurping ]

172
00:06:00.628 --> 00:06:02.129
That's the amphitheater.

173
00:06:02.163 --> 00:06:03.396
[ Coughs ]
Great place to get fucked.

174
00:06:03.430 --> 00:06:04.932
[ Screaming ]

175
00:06:04.966 --> 00:06:06.200
That's the archery range.

176
00:06:06.234 --> 00:06:08.002
Perfect place to get fucked.

177
00:06:08.035 --> 00:06:09.337
That's the cafeteria.

178
00:06:09.369 --> 00:06:10.938
Super awesome place --
We get it.

179
00:06:10.972 --> 00:06:13.708
But where does everything else.
like. come from?

180
00:06:13.741 --> 00:06:15.209
A bunch of us have
trust funds.

181
00:06:15.243 --> 00:06:17.044
so we just DoorDash
anything we want.

182
00:06:17.078 --> 00:06:19.313
Greek food incoming.

183
00:06:19.347 --> 00:06:21.215
And... <i>no</i> tip.

184
00:06:21.249 --> 00:06:23.517
What. I didn't see
him make it.

185
00:06:23.551 --> 00:06:27.054
Excuse me.
Edward Merlot Hands
coming through.

186
00:06:27.088 --> 00:06:29.957
Look. you're the first kid
to show up here in ages.

187
00:06:29.991 --> 00:06:31.025
So. uh...

188
00:06:31.058 --> 00:06:32.392
Do you two solemnly swear

189
00:06:32.425 --> 00:06:34.996
to dedicate your life
to the party?

190
00:06:35.930 --> 00:06:37.765
[ Party music thumping ]

191
00:06:37.798 --> 00:06:39.600
Woop woop!
Yeah! [ Chuckles ]

192
00:06:39.634 --> 00:06:41.468
I'm gonna party 'til my face
fucking face melts off!

193
00:06:41.502 --> 00:06:44.105
[ Woman vocalizing ]

194
00:06:44.138 --> 00:06:46.807
Well. I guess being
high forever isn't all bad.

195
00:06:46.841 --> 00:06:48.676
I'll lose my job and --
and -- and. uh.

196
00:06:48.709 --> 00:06:50.645
try to understand
Jackson Pollock paintings.

197
00:06:50.678 --> 00:06:52.479
It was a visualization
of suicide.

198
00:06:52.513 --> 00:06:54.315
Aw. it totally was.

199
00:06:54.348 --> 00:06:55.816
You ruined it!

200
00:06:55.850 --> 00:06:57.518
Are we really gonna be
high forever?

201
00:06:57.551 --> 00:06:58.819
C-Can we Google this?

202
00:06:58.853 --> 00:07:01.088
[Giggles ]
We can Google anything.

203
00:07:01.122 --> 00:07:03.456
[ Keyboard clicking ]

204
00:07:04.125 --> 00:07:05.293
Oh. Jer Bear. look!

205
00:07:05.326 --> 00:07:06.794
They have some
version of Narcan

206
00:07:06.827 --> 00:07:08.329
at a pharmacy
the next solar system over.

207
00:07:08.362 --> 00:07:09.897
How are we supposed
to get there?

208
00:07:09.931 --> 00:07:12.166
My dad has a way to hail
space cabs in the garage.

209
00:07:12.199 --> 00:07:14.302
Come on.
How's this not needing him?

210
00:07:14.335 --> 00:07:17.505
Cause we're doing it
behind his back.

211
00:07:17.538 --> 00:07:20.074
[ Woman vocalizing ]

212
00:07:20.107 --> 00:07:22.843
How do these work again?

213
00:07:22.877 --> 00:07:25.146
Like this. watch.

214
00:07:25.179 --> 00:07:26.446
[ Grunts softly ]
Oh. wow.

215
00:07:26.479 --> 00:07:28.382
[ Chuckling ]
[ Body thumping ]

216
00:07:28.416 --> 00:07:30.151
Oh. that's way easier!

217
00:07:30.184 --> 00:07:31.519
You can't back out
of this deal.

218
00:07:31.552 --> 00:07:33.287
I got a pallet full
of people-sized carrots.

219
00:07:33.321 --> 00:07:35.356
[ Speaking indistinctly
over phone ]
"Not your problem?"

220
00:07:35.389 --> 00:07:37.658
Oh. it's about to be.

221
00:07:37.692 --> 00:07:39.492
If we make
irregular rhythms...

222
00:07:39.527 --> 00:07:41.829
...he can't hear us
under there.
[ Shudders ]

223
00:07:41.862 --> 00:07:45.066
He's your dad.
not the god of Arrakis.

224
00:07:45.099 --> 00:07:47.335
[ Satellite chimes. beeps ]

225
00:07:47.368 --> 00:07:49.503
All right. Zarz Dinnarz
will be here

226
00:07:49.537 --> 00:07:52.306
in what I'm guessing
is three minutes --

227
00:07:52.340 --> 00:07:54.542
[ Slug smacks ]
Oh. that was seconds.

228
00:07:54.575 --> 00:07:57.378
Hey! For. um. Rick?

229
00:07:57.411 --> 00:07:59.180
You may enter me.

230
00:07:59.814 --> 00:08:00.982
Uh. okay.

231
00:08:01.015 --> 00:08:02.683
[ Squelching ]

232
00:08:02.717 --> 00:08:04.518
Please sit still.
Ah!

233
00:08:04.552 --> 00:08:07.487
I have taken a form
your butts desire.

234
00:08:07.521 --> 00:08:08.889
[ Panting ]

235
00:08:08.923 --> 00:08:10.358
Oh. my God.
this is the exact limo

236
00:08:10.391 --> 00:08:11.425
we took to prom.

237
00:08:11.459 --> 00:08:13.761
Those can't be <i>real</i> pretzels?

238
00:08:13.794 --> 00:08:15.363
[ Bottle pops ]
Oh. isn't this amazing?

239
00:08:15.396 --> 00:08:17.497
It's like we're hanging out
as kids again.

240
00:08:17.531 --> 00:08:20.334
Oh. everything's slick
like a womb.

241
00:08:20.368 --> 00:08:22.069
Oh. I need to get baby-sized.

242
00:08:22.103 --> 00:08:24.705
If I'm born. I'll rip my mother
from crack to crack!

243
00:08:24.739 --> 00:08:25.906
Everything okay back there?

244
00:08:25.940 --> 00:08:28.042
Uh. do you have
an umbilical cord?

245
00:08:28.075 --> 00:08:30.311
What? Are you people high?

246
00:08:30.344 --> 00:08:31.879
Oh. we shouldn't
have done this. Beth.

247
00:08:31.912 --> 00:08:33.381
We're too old to be this high.

248
00:08:33.414 --> 00:08:35.750
Oh. sweetie.
I'm right here with you.

249
00:08:35.783 --> 00:08:37.785
You're safe.
We're safe.

250
00:08:37.818 --> 00:08:39.887
[ Breathing deeply ]
[ Panting ]

251
00:08:41.255 --> 00:08:43.357
[ Sighs in relief ]
Mm.

252
00:08:43.391 --> 00:08:44.792
Wow.

253
00:08:44.825 --> 00:08:46.827
It's like prom night
all over again.

254
00:08:46.861 --> 00:08:48.496
You found the right hole
eventually.

255
00:08:48.529 --> 00:08:49.797
Where's the moonroof?

256
00:08:49.830 --> 00:08:51.298
I need -- I need
to tell the universe

257
00:08:51.332 --> 00:08:52.366
that Beth Sanchez
is the best thing

258
00:08:52.400 --> 00:08:54.035
that's ever happened to me.

259
00:08:54.068 --> 00:08:56.037
Uh. what? Please remain seated.
Aw. Jer.

260
00:08:56.070 --> 00:08:58.739
But how will the cosmos
know how I feel?

261
00:08:58.773 --> 00:09:00.441
[ Splat. squelch! ]

262
00:09:00.474 --> 00:09:02.143
[ Laughing excitedly ]

263
00:09:02.643 --> 00:09:04.045
[ Screams ]

264
00:09:04.078 --> 00:09:05.913
Zarz: My dermis!

265
00:09:05.946 --> 00:09:07.448
[ Squelching ]

266
00:09:07.481 --> 00:09:09.083
[ Whirs ]

267
00:09:09.116 --> 00:09:10.484
Jerry: Ah!
Oh. my God!

268
00:09:10.519 --> 00:09:13.087
[ Loud crashing ]

269
00:09:13.120 --> 00:09:14.989
[ Shoppers gasp ]

270
00:09:15.022 --> 00:09:17.024
Whoo!
[ Beth and Jerry giggling ]

271
00:09:19.693 --> 00:09:23.197
[ Weakly ] Thank you
for choosing Zarz Dinnarz.

272
00:09:23.230 --> 00:09:24.932
Oh. my gosh. is he dying?

273
00:09:24.965 --> 00:09:27.568
[ Yawning ]
No. I'm just tired.

274
00:09:27.601 --> 00:09:30.671
I've been doing a lot
of airport runs at night.

