00:10:16.484 --> 00:10:18.553
[ Porta Potties thudding ]

299
00:10:18.587 --> 00:10:20.721
[ Both screaming ]

300
00:10:22.089 --> 00:10:24.225
[ Both groaning ]

301
00:10:25.726 --> 00:10:27.361
Bitch. move.

302
00:10:27.394 --> 00:10:32.199
These assholes have way more
stamina for being assholes.

303
00:10:32.233 --> 00:10:36.203
Boys. Margo's gonna blow!

304
00:10:36.237 --> 00:10:37.572
[ Grunting ]
[ Chuckles ]

305
00:10:37.606 --> 00:10:39.240
[ Explosive fart.
Fart Baby whines ]

306
00:10:39.273 --> 00:10:41.008
Oh. look at that.
a Fart Baby!

307
00:10:41.041 --> 00:10:43.310
What the fuck!
Oh. my God.

308
00:10:43.344 --> 00:10:45.312
False alarm.
Just another baby.

309
00:10:45.346 --> 00:10:46.881
Get that Fart Baby a beer!

310
00:10:46.914 --> 00:10:49.350
Campers: Chug! Chug! Chug! Chug!

311
00:10:49.383 --> 00:10:51.185
Is that kid gonna be okay?

312
00:10:51.218 --> 00:10:52.453
Fart Baby? Yeah. man.

313
00:10:52.486 --> 00:10:53.687
He will be if he parties.

314
00:10:53.721 --> 00:10:55.055
Fart Baby party!

315
00:10:55.089 --> 00:10:56.390
Dude. this has gotten
out of hand.

316
00:10:56.423 --> 00:10:57.691
Yeah. we gotta
bounce before

317
00:10:57.725 --> 00:10:59.460
we turn into
even bigger assholes.

318
00:10:59.493 --> 00:11:01.495
What's this talk
about leavin'?

319
00:11:01.530 --> 00:11:03.797
Yeah. we're having
a good time. right?

320
00:11:03.831 --> 00:11:06.901
Kind of feels like
we aren't free to go.

321
00:11:06.934 --> 00:11:08.169
Isn't that
technically a rule?

322
00:11:08.202 --> 00:11:09.870
Nah. man.

323
00:11:09.904 --> 00:11:11.405
Besides. all that's out there
is that shitty ass town.

324
00:11:11.438 --> 00:11:12.740
We just need to call
our grandpa.

325
00:11:12.773 --> 00:11:14.074
No phone calls.
Okay.

326
00:11:14.108 --> 00:11:16.177
I'm sorry.
but see. that's two rules.

327
00:11:16.210 --> 00:11:17.378
Fuck that shit.

328
00:11:17.411 --> 00:11:18.679
You guys took
an oath to rage.

329
00:11:18.712 --> 00:11:20.414
and now you want
to skip out on one?

330
00:11:20.447 --> 00:11:22.983
Yeah. I'm starting to get a real
lame vibe from these two.

331
00:11:23.017 --> 00:11:26.787
And you saw the dead pile
of lame people. right?

332
00:11:26.820 --> 00:11:28.623
[ Fart Baby cries ]

333
00:11:28.657 --> 00:11:29.823
Oh. now look what you did.

334
00:11:29.857 --> 00:11:31.158
Fart Baby's crying.

335
00:11:31.192 --> 00:11:32.760
It's okay. Fart Baby.

336
00:11:32.793 --> 00:11:34.094
They're not going anywhere.

337
00:11:34.128 --> 00:11:35.196
They're gonna rage.

338
00:11:35.229 --> 00:11:37.164
Oh. no. no. We're cool.

339
00:11:37.198 --> 00:11:38.899
Then prove it.

340
00:11:40.201 --> 00:11:41.969
[ Can pops ]

341
00:11:42.002 --> 00:11:44.939
[ Fart Baby whines. cries ]

342
00:11:44.972 --> 00:11:49.143
I wish we hadn't given
beer to that baby.
[ Panting ]

343
00:11:49.743 --> 00:11:51.513
[ Exhales ]

344
00:11:51.546 --> 00:11:54.782
Oh. Beth.
I had the strangest dream

345
00:11:54.815 --> 00:11:57.318
we got high forever.

346
00:11:59.053 --> 00:12:03.357
Yeah. this makes
a lot more sense.

347
00:12:03.390 --> 00:12:06.393
[ Nervously ]Uh. honey.
how long have we been here?

348
00:12:06.427 --> 00:12:07.761
Couple days? Couple weeks?

349
00:12:07.795 --> 00:12:09.930
This store planet has
an artificial sky.

350
00:12:09.964 --> 00:12:11.465
[ Gasps ] Jerry. look!

351
00:12:12.800 --> 00:12:14.301
[ Phone beeps ]

352
00:12:16.770 --> 00:12:18.439
[ Phone beeps ]
Damn it!

353
00:12:18.472 --> 00:12:20.341
It's in jail
with the deodorant.

354
00:12:20.374 --> 00:12:21.942
Hologram: <i>Paging associate.</i>
<i>please wait.</i>
[ Dinging ]

355
00:12:21.976 --> 00:12:23.911
Okay. [chuckles]
he's on his way.

356
00:12:23.944 --> 00:12:26.514
<i>Paging associate.</i>
<i>Please wait.</i>
[ Chuckles ]

357
00:12:28.182 --> 00:12:29.718
<i>Paging associate.</i>
<i>Please wait.</i>

358
00:12:29.750 --> 00:12:31.586
Because he was
a bus ride away. Right.

359
00:12:31.620 --> 00:12:33.754
The whole planet is a mall.

360
00:12:33.787 --> 00:12:35.856
<i>Paging associate.</i>
<i>Please wait.</i>
I hope he gets here soon.

361
00:12:35.889 --> 00:12:37.925
[ Gasps ] Oh. my God.
Oh.

362
00:12:37.958 --> 00:12:39.661
<i>Paging associate.</i>
<i>Please wait.</i>
He's at an airport.

363
00:12:39.694 --> 00:12:42.029
I can't take this anymore.
Connecting flight?!

364
00:12:42.062 --> 00:12:43.732
[ Glass breaks. alarm blaring ]

365
00:12:43.764 --> 00:12:45.933
Security guard:
Hey. stop right there!

366
00:12:45.966 --> 00:12:47.301
Jerry: Oh!
Beth: Yes!

367
00:12:47.334 --> 00:12:49.103
[ Both screaming ]

368
00:12:49.770 --> 00:12:51.506
Whoo!
[ Elevator dings ]

369
00:12:53.941 --> 00:12:55.776
[ Grunts ]
[ Segway whirs ]

370
00:12:55.809 --> 00:12:58.078
[ Both grunt ]

371
00:12:58.112 --> 00:12:59.179
Did it work?

372
00:12:59.213 --> 00:13:02.651
Are we un-high?

373
00:13:02.684 --> 00:13:03.884
[ Phone beeps ]

374
00:13:03.917 --> 00:13:06.453
We have too few hearts. Jerry.

375
00:13:06.487 --> 00:13:08.289
Too few hearts!

376
00:13:08.322 --> 00:13:10.257
Beth. I called Rick.

377
00:13:10.291 --> 00:13:11.660
What?!

378
00:13:11.693 --> 00:13:13.695
You have a cosmic
safety net for a dad.

379
00:13:13.728 --> 00:13:14.895
Embrace it.

380
00:13:14.928 --> 00:13:16.631
Well. that makes me
feel like a baby.

381
00:13:16.665 --> 00:13:18.533
It's okay to be
a baby sometimes.

382
00:13:18.566 --> 00:13:20.568
I've been a baby our
entire marriage.

383
00:13:20.602 --> 00:13:22.570
But we should all get a turn.

384
00:13:22.604 --> 00:13:23.904
Well.

385
00:13:23.937 --> 00:13:25.573
Well. I -- I did have fun.

386
00:13:25.607 --> 00:13:26.741
Me too.

387
00:13:26.775 --> 00:13:29.843
Oh. <i>now</i> I'm invited to hang.

388
00:13:29.877 --> 00:13:31.546
Whoa! [ Thuds. groans ]

389
00:13:31.579 --> 00:13:37.885
Oh. everyone wants grandpa's
help. but <i>nobody</i> wants grandpa.

390
00:13:37.918 --> 00:13:40.154
If we had a car.
I'd roll the windows up.

391
00:13:40.187 --> 00:13:41.855
Summer:
Bars have phones. right?

392
00:13:41.889 --> 00:13:43.324
[ Music plays faintly ]

393
00:13:43.357 --> 00:13:44.759
Well. woo!

394
00:13:44.793 --> 00:13:46.093
Look who came
down the mountain

395
00:13:46.126 --> 00:13:48.763
to grace <i>us</i>
with their presence.

396
00:13:48.797 --> 00:13:50.765
I didn't think
you camp assholes

397
00:13:50.799 --> 00:13:51.899
ever left your bubble.

398
00:13:51.932 --> 00:13:53.500
Who gives a shit. lady?

399
00:13:53.535 --> 00:13:55.704
This may be a literal
matter of life and death.

400
00:13:55.737 --> 00:13:57.338
Can we phone our grandfather?

401
00:13:57.371 --> 00:13:59.106
Did not hear a "please."

402
00:13:59.139 --> 00:14:00.775
Fine. please!
Bitch. oh. my God!

403
00:14:00.809 --> 00:14:02.109
"Bitch?" 'Scuse me?

404
00:14:02.142 --> 00:14:04.411
I don't think
you can reclaim words.

405
00:14:04.445 --> 00:14:05.879
so I don't appreciate that.

406
00:14:05.913 --> 00:14:08.516
Oh. my God.
thank you so much.
One call.

407
00:14:08.550 --> 00:14:10.050
What's his number?
12.

408
00:14:10.084 --> 00:14:12.386
12? That's a phone number?

409
00:14:12.419 --> 00:14:14.455
[ Phone dialing. ringing ]

410
00:14:15.889 --> 00:14:17.458
Grandpa Rick.
you need to come get us!

411
00:14:17.491 --> 00:14:19.026
The campers killed
the guards and counselors.

412
00:14:19.059 --> 00:14:20.762
and now they're living
it up by themselves

413
00:14:20.795 --> 00:14:22.764
and won't let us leave
and I know it seems like

414
00:14:22.797 --> 00:14:24.431
we've learned nothing
but we're done being
spoiled assholes.

415
00:14:24.465 --> 00:14:26.333
Rick: <i>Hep- [coughs]</i>
<i>here's the thing.</i>

416
00:14:26.367 --> 00:14:28.235
<i>[ Giggles. coughs]</i>

417
00:14:28.268 --> 00:14:29.738
Rick? H-Hello?

418
00:14:29.771 --> 00:14:31.472
<i>[ Laughs ]</i>

419
00:14:31.506 --> 00:14:33.407
[ Unintelligible muttering ]

420
00:14:33.440 --> 00:14:35.309
<i>Bye.</i> [ Line clicks ]

421
00:14:35.342 --> 00:14:36.845
Okay. what the fuck?

422
00:14:36.877 --> 00:14:39.413
Couldn't help but hear
there's a load of rich kids

423
00:14:39.446 --> 00:14:43.450
up at that camp
completely unsupervised.

424
00:14:43.484 --> 00:14:46.253
Oh. not -- not sure if.
uh. there's a reason

425
00:14:46.286 --> 00:14:47.856
<i>everyone</i> needs to know that.

426
00:14:47.888 --> 00:14:49.957
Oh. there is.
[ Shotgun cocks ]

427
00:14:49.990 --> 00:14:52.226
It's visiting day.

428
00:14:52.259 --> 00:14:54.328
For our guns.

429
00:14:54.361 --> 00:14:57.398
Am I high
or are the kids in danger?

430
00:14:57.431 --> 00:14:59.900
Both. [ Chuckles ]

431
00:14:59.933 --> 00:15:01.636
We're being punished
by the universe.

432
00:15:01.669 --> 00:15:04.104
Beth. slap me.
I-It'll sober me up.

433
00:15:04.138 --> 00:15:06.240
[ Groans ]
Ow! Ow!

434
00:15:06.273 --> 00:15:09.677
Did you see how I went
up and back down?
[ Thuds ]

435
00:15:09.711 --> 00:15:11.746
Dad. we need to save
the kids in a way

436
00:15:11.780 --> 00:15:13.414
where they think
we're not fuckups

437
00:15:13.447 --> 00:15:14.915
they can just blow off.

438
00:15:14.948 --> 00:15:18.586
Okay. okay. just --
just give me a sec.

439
00:15:18.620 --> 00:15:20.889
Dad!
Am I not standing yet?

440
00:15:20.921 --> 00:15:22.189
[ Grunts ]

441
00:15:22.222 --> 00:15:25.025
Why are you s-so dense?
[ Groaning ]

442
00:15:26.326 --> 00:15:28.696
[ Grumbling ]

443
00:15:28.730 --> 00:15:30.431
Carry the two...

444
00:15:30.464 --> 00:15:32.266
All right. All right.

445
00:15:32.299 --> 00:15:34.502
Kiiiids. home!

446
00:15:35.870 --> 00:15:36.970
[ Cart smacks ]

447
00:15:37.004 --> 00:15:39.406
Ow. Did it work?

448
00:15:40.007 --> 00:15:42.242
Are you Rick?

449
00:15:42.276 --> 00:15:44.077
Yes.

450
00:15:44.111 --> 00:15:48.182
The -- the same Rick
we just pushed through?

451
00:15:48.215 --> 00:15:50.184
Oh. God.
[ Portal sloshes ]

452
00:15:50.217 --> 00:15:52.119
I-Is this where the kids are?

453
00:15:52.152 --> 00:15:53.855
I'm too fuckin' high
for this.

454
00:15:53.888 --> 00:15:55.155
We pushed you through...

455
00:15:55.189 --> 00:15:59.026
...and you came out.

456
00:16:00.327 --> 00:16:01.696
Ah!

457
00:16:02.630 --> 00:16:04.899
Do you feel different?

458
00:16:04.933 --> 00:16:06.801
Uh. I don't know.

459
00:16:06.835 --> 00:16:10.705
[ Groaning in despair ]
Do I?

460
00:16:10.738 --> 00:16:13.106
Lintana:
Okey dokey. artichokey.

461
00:16:13.140 --> 00:16:15.577
It's ransom tiiiime.

462
00:16:15.610 --> 00:16:17.978
We googled your parents.
and I gotta tell you something.

463
00:16:18.011 --> 00:16:21.281
you kids are some real
silver spoon fucks.

464
00:16:21.315 --> 00:16:23.651
Except for you two --
you two aren't rich at all.

465
00:16:23.685 --> 00:16:25.319
Ouch.
Hurtful.

466
00:16:25.352 --> 00:16:28.656
What'll be <i>"hurtful"</i> is if
we don't get our money.

467
00:16:28.690 --> 00:16:31.693
So you better pray mommy
and daddy pick up the phone.

468
00:16:31.726 --> 00:16:34.361
Yeah? Let's hit it. boys.

469
00:16:34.394 --> 00:16:35.496
[ Door shuts ]

470
00:16:35.530 --> 00:16:36.698
We're screwed.

471
00:16:36.731 --> 00:16:37.998
Someone's folks will pay up.

472
00:16:38.031 --> 00:16:39.534
and we'll be out of here
in no time.

473
00:16:39.567 --> 00:16:40.702
You don't know that.

474
00:16:40.735 --> 00:16:42.102
All of our parents
left us here

475
00:16:42.135 --> 00:16:43.838
because we're spoiled
pieces of shit.

476
00:16:43.872 --> 00:16:45.740
M-Maybe they aren't
ever coming back.

477
00:16:45.773 --> 00:16:47.809
[ Portal whirs ]
Oh. thank Christ.

478
00:16:47.842 --> 00:16:50.077
[ Gasps ] It's different.

479
00:16:50.110 --> 00:16:51.713
Wow. [laughs] it is.

480
00:16:51.746 --> 00:16:54.414
H-h-hey. Morty! You're here.

481
00:16:54.448 --> 00:16:56.551
Rick. get us out
of this nightmare.

482
00:16:56.584 --> 00:16:59.253
S-sure thing. Morty.

483
00:16:59.286 --> 00:17:01.421
Mortyyyyy.

484
00:17:01.455 --> 00:17:03.123
Mortyyyy.

485
00:17:03.156 --> 00:17:04.826
I like that.
What the --

486
00:17:04.859 --> 00:17:06.226
[ Thuds ]
Quit messing around.

487
00:17:06.260 --> 00:17:07.795
Where's the portal gun?

488
00:17:07.829 --> 00:17:09.029
I think I --

489
00:17:09.062 --> 00:17:11.031
I think I left it
in the shopping cart.

490
00:17:11.064 --> 00:17:13.902
Did you guys smoke
my High Forever?
What?

491
00:17:13.935 --> 00:17:15.369
Look at me.

492
00:17:15.402 --> 00:17:16.270
Look at me.

493
00:17:16.303 --> 00:17:17.739
You can't get angry. Summer.

494
00:17:17.772 --> 00:17:19.306
I gave it to you. Probably.

495
00:17:19.339 --> 00:17:21.543
Oh. my God.
Wow. They're out
of their gourds.

496
00:17:21.576 --> 00:17:23.043
We are zooted.

497
00:17:23.076 --> 00:17:24.946
<i>This</i> is why
we've been acting out.

498
00:17:24.979 --> 00:17:27.247
Because we have absolute
psychos as role models.

499
00:17:27.281 --> 00:17:28.950
You guys are bad parents.

500
00:17:28.983 --> 00:17:31.285
Boo! [ Laughs ]

501
00:17:31.318 --> 00:17:33.420
This version of
everyone's mean.

502
00:17:33.453 --> 00:17:34.488
You know what?

503
